President Obama spoke with General John Allen, Commander of U.S. Forces and the NATO International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan, regarding the ongoing violence in Afghanistan and the killing of two U.S. servicemembers. The President offered his condolences to General Allen and the families affected. He also thanked General Allen for his efforts to protect servicemembers and civilians in Afghanistan and promote calm. President Karzai's statement calling for peaceful expressions and dialogue was welcomed. The United States remains committed to partnering with Afghanistan to combat al Qaeda and strengthen the Afghan state.